# Level 2 Step 1 Hard
## Exercise 4 from Hasib

### b. View detail of dev/md0
```bash
mdadm --detail /dev/md0
```
### Check disks
```bash
lsblk
```
### d. Check Physical Volume Assignment
```bash
pvs
```
### e. Check Volume Groups
```bash
vgs
```

### Display Volume Group Information
```bash
vgdisplay vg0
```

### Verify the volume vg0 is mounted
```bash
df -h | grep vg0
```









## Exercise 4
### Create the RAID 6 array
#### a) Create RAID6 array
mdadm --create /dev/md0 --level=6 --raid-devices=4 /dev/sdb /dev/sdc /dev/sdd /dev/sde --spare-devices=2 /dev/sdf /dev/sdg

#### b) Verify array layout
cat /proc/mdstat

mdadm --detail /dev/md0

#### c) To verify 
lsblk

### d) To create physical volumes on 2additional disks
pvcreate /dev/md0 /dev/sdh /dev/sdi

#### To check
pvs

### e) To create group of LVM(LogicaL Volume Manager)volumes containing physical volumes 
vgcreate vg0 /dev/md0 /dev/sdh

#### To check:
vgdisplay vg0



## Exercise 6
### Disk Names

* nvme0n2
* nvme0n3
* nvme0n4
* nvme0n5
* nvme0n6

### Package Source Path
Append "contrib non-free" after each line main
```bash
nano /etc/apt/sources.list
```

### Check ZFS

```bash
zfs version
```

### Command to list all block devices:
```bash
lsblk
```

### Command to check pool status:
```bash
zpool status userpool
```

### Confirm /userpool and /userpool/users are mounted:
```bash
zfs list
```

### Test IO benchmark using dd and /dev/urandom
```bash
dd if=/dev/urandom of=/userpool/users/testfile.bin bs=1M count=10 oflag=dsync
```
### Clean/Remove the test file

```bash
rm /userpool/users/zfs_testfile.bin
```
